The paper deals with approximation algorithms for graph parameters related to intersection graphs of geometric objects, such as boxes and cubes. This falls under the scope of computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also mentions related problems in poset theory and graph theory, which are areas of research in computer science theory (cs.DS, cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses approximation algorithms for optimization problems, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT).
